    "Increased awareness of these biases enables healthcare providers to critically evaluate LLM outputs, mitigating potential harms and promoting more equitable patient care 16.",
    "Previously, the integration of algorithms into health information systems focused on developing AI models to address specific clinical questions and workflow inefficiencies, such as Clinical Decision Support Systems (CDSS) for evidence-based recommendations, predictive analytics for forecasting patient outcomes, and automating complex coding and billing processes.",
    "These AI tools, built from limited subsets of clinical data extracted from medical records, were typically accessible only to healthcare professionals and billing specialists 17, 18.",
    "Research involving conventional AI that falls under the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) definition of Software as a Medical Device is subject to oversight, primarily through FDA and IRB supervision, as the device undergoes testing and validation 19.",
    "Commercial generative AI systems, such as those that use large language models (LLMs), were not initially designed as medical devices and therefore typically lack regulatory oversight throughout their development-from inception to validation."
  ],
